================================================================================
Derivation and attribution
================================================================================

crustagent is a from-scratch Rust implementation of the classic Microsoft Agent
character system. Its file-format parsing and playback behavior were
reverse-engineered from — and, for several algorithms, ported from — the source
of:

  DoubleAgent
  Copyright (C) Cinnamon Software Inc.
  https://sourceforge.net/projects/doubleagent/
  Licensed GPL / LGPL.

DoubleAgent is offered under the GPL or the LGPL; crustagent takes the LGPL
option and is distributed under the GNU Lesser General Public License, version 3
or later. Portions of the following modules in particular follow DoubleAgent's
implementation closely and are best understood as ports of it:

  - crustagent-format: the ACS 2.0 / ACS 1.5 readers, the LZ77 image
    decompressor (CAgentFileBinary::DecodeData), and the frame compositor
    (CAgentFile::GetFrameBits).
  - crustagent-core: the animation sequence builder
    (CAgentStreamInfo::SequenceAnimationFrames) and the speech-markup parser
    (CAgentTextParse).

Other parts — the embedding API and action queue (crustagent), the windowed
renderer (crustagent-render), the text-to-speech and audio integration
(crustagent-tts, crustagent-audio), and the GIF encoder (crustagent-gif) — are
original to this project.

================================================================================
Microsoft Agent
================================================================================

The ".acs" character file format and the Microsoft Agent characters (Clippit,
Merlin, Genie, Peedy, Robby, etc.) and their artwork are the property of
Microsoft Corporation and the respective character authors. "Microsoft" and
"Microsoft Agent" are trademarks of Microsoft Corporation. This project is not
affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by Microsoft.

No Microsoft Agent character assets (.acs / .acf / .aca / .acd files or their
artwork or sounds) are included in this repository. Character files are supplied
by the user at runtime.

